The paper proposes adversarial attacks for Reinforcement Learning (RL) and improves the robustness of Deep Reinforcement Learning algorithms (DRL) to parameter uncertainties. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these sub-categories are closely related to the topics covered in the paper. However, given that the paper focuses on improving the robustness of DRL algorithms, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
